Minister of Information, Culture, Arts and Sports Innocent Bashungwa has applauded Tanzania Standard Newspapers, (TSN), publishers of the state-run newspapers, for diligence, commitment and efficiency towards work. Speaking during an official tour of the public company today (December 14, 2020), the minister said journalists producing the country’s oldest paper, Daily News, do their work professionally and ethically. “This paper has been the country’s icon and we promise increased cooperation to ensure it thrives and survives in the dissemination of information to the public,” he said. He also praised the company for its creativity in launching a digital platform named Daily News Digital.